csrf token is used to avoid csrf attacks
this attacks takes place with the help of session cookies that are stored by a web browser whenever you login to a site for that particular site.
now since the cookies are stored in your browser an attacker can make you submit a form unknowingly by making the form automatic submit.
this will lead to make attacker use the form that was CSRF vulnerable to use that particular form according to your use.
- cross site request forgery

 A request is "same-site" if its target's URI's origin's registrable
   domain is an exact match for the request's initiator's "site for
   cookies", and "cross-site" otherwise.